PART 8: Definitive sign test at n=3,5,7
======================================================================
  n=3 full table:
    bits=000 (0): Ps=-1, pop=0, H=1
    bits=001 (1): Ps=+1, pop=1, H=1
    bits=010 (2): Ps=-3, pop=1, H=3
    bits=011 (3): Ps=-1, pop=2, H=1
    bits=100 (4): Ps=+1, pop=1, H=1
    bits=101 (5): Ps=+3, pop=2, H=3
    bits=110 (6): Ps=-1, pop=2, H=1
    bits=111 (7): Ps=+1, pop=3, H=1

  n=3 lambda classes:
    lambda=(0, 0, 0): [(0, -1), (1, 1), (3, -1), (4, 1), (6, -1), (7, 1)]
    lambda=(1, 1, 1): [(2, -3), (5, 3)]

  CORRECT CLAIM:
  Within each labeled lambda class, all tournaments with same sign(Ps)
  have the same popcount parity. This does NOT mean (-1)^pop = sign(Ps) globally.

